cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a self-correction method for the Min-Sum decoding of LDPC codes, which is a topic related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - LDPC codes are widely used in communication systems, and the proposed method can potentially improve the performance of such systems. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the performance of the proposed method through Monte-Carlo simulations, which can be considered as a network simulation. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a modification to the variable node processing in the Min-Sum decoding algorithm, which can be seen as an algorithmic improvement. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper emphasizes the low complexity of the proposed method, which can be relevant to the study of computational complexity.
